    "body": "We can't simply expose a `miri_terminate_current_thread` shim to turn a thread state to `Terminated`.\n\nWe should run MIR steps to normally finish the task and `kernel_task_entry` to have kmiri clean  up the stack.\n\nIt basically means that calls in `kernel_task_entry` should always return, otherwise https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/97 will be hit.\n\nSo  `miri_terminate_current_thread` becomes useless, and should be removed.",
